/*
  Localizable.strings (English — development language)

  Marmot's UI strings are written as literals in SwiftUI, which look up this
  table automatically at runtime (key = the English literal). English needs no
  entries because a missing key falls back to itself.

  To add a language:
  1. Copy this folder to <code>.lproj (e.g. de.lproj, fr.lproj, ja.lproj)
  2. Add one line per string you translate:  "English text" = "Translation";
  3. Build — the Makefile bundles every *.lproj folder automatically.

  Example entries a German translation would start with:

  "Scan My Mac" = "Meinen Mac scannen";
  "Dry Run" = "Probelauf";
  "Apply" = "Anwenden";
*/
